          <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="Body Table" translate="true">A new </text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">segment</text><text styleclass="Body Table" translate="true"> is now in the motion, and it becomes t</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">he </text><text styleclass="Element-Header" translate="true">Selected-Segment.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="Body Table" translate="true">The new segment has a </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Segment-Width" styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">Segment-Width</link><text styleclass="Body Table" translate="true"> = </text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">90º </text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">(</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">or an equivalent value for other X–axis </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Edit-Active-Motion-Settings" anchor="Motion" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">units</link><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">).</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Use</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Segment-Editor" styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">Segment Editor</link><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> to reduce the </text><text styleclass="Parameter-Header" translate="true">Segment-Width</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> of segments, and so reduce the </text><text styleclass="Parameter-Header" translate="true">Motion-Width</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> again.</text></para>
